## Commit Guidelines

### Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Example Commits

```bash
# Feature
git commit -m "feat(tournaments): add live tournament filter

- Added live filter button to tournament list
- Implements real-time filtering of active tournaments
- Improves user experience for browsing live events"

# Bug Fix
git commit -m "fix(auth): resolve login crash on invalid email

- Handle null pointer exception in email validation
- Add proper error handling for Firebase auth failures
- Fixes issue #123"

# Documentation
git commit -m "docs: update setup instructions for Firebase

- Add step-by-step Firebase configuration guide
- Include troubleshooting section for common issues"

# Refactor
git commit -m "refactor(ui): simplify tournament card layout

- Extract common styling logic
- Reduce code duplication by 30%
- Improve maintainability"
```

### Commit Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation changes |
| `style` | Code style changes (formatting, etc.) |
| `refactor` | Code refactoring |
| `perf` | Performance improvements |
| `test` | Test additions/changes |
| `chore` | Build, dependencies, etc. |

---

## Pull Request Process

### Before Submitting PR

- [ ] Code follows project style guidelines
- [ ] All tests pass: `./gradlew test`
- [ ] New code includes appropriate tests
- [ ] Documentation is updated
- [ ] Commit messages are clear and descriptive
- [ ] No merge conflicts with main branch
- [ ] No sensitive information is committed

### PR Description Template

```markdown
## Description
Brief description of changes

## Type of Change
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation update

## Related Issue
Closes #(issue number)

## Changes Made
- Change 1
- Change 2
- Change 3

## Testing Done
- [ ] Unit tests written
- [ ] Manual testing completed
- [ ] No new warnings

## Screenshots (if applicable)
Add screenshots for UI changes

## Checklist
- [ ] Code follows style guidelines
- [ ] Tests pass locally
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] No breaking changes
```

### PR Review Process

1. **Automatic Checks**
   - Tests must pass
   - Code style verified
   - Merge conflicts resolved

2. **Code Review**
   - Maintainers review code
   - Feedback provided
   - Discussion on changes

3. **Approval & Merge**
   - At least 2 approvals required
   - Maintainer merges PR
   - Branch is deleted

---

## Testing Guidelines

### Writing Tests

```kotlin
import org.junit.Test
import org.junit.Before
import androidx.test.ext.junit.runners.AndroidJUnit4

@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)
class TournamentModelTest {
    
    private lateinit var tournament: TournamentModel
    
    @Before
    fun setUp() {
        tournament = TournamentModel(
            id = "1",
            title = "Test Tournament",
            prizePool = 100000.0,
            entryFee = 500.0
        )
    }
    
    @Test
    fun testTournamentCreation() {
        assertEquals("Test Tournament", tournament.title)
        assertEquals(100000.0, tournament.prizePool)
    }
    
    @Test
    fun testTournamentValidation() {
        assertTrue(tournament.isValid())
    }
}
```

### Running Tests

```bash
# Unit tests
./gradlew test

# Instrumented tests
./gradlew connectedAndroidTest

# Specific test class
./gradlew test --tests TournamentModelTest

# With coverage
./gradlew testDebugUnitTest

# View test results
# Open: app/build/reports/tests/testDebugUnitTest/index.html
```

### Test Coverage Requirements

- Minimum 70% code coverage for new code
- All critical functions must have tests
- Edge cases and error scenarios tested

